[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Through a number of 
[normal]forums
[normal], operators engage with each other and with the industry. These include
[normal], but are not limited to
[normal]:
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]5.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In September 2013, 
[normal]in addition to the above forums
[normal], the main operators established a Joint Operators Review (JOR) Working Group to further share best practice, to identify any changes that we can make, and to drive improvements in a coordinated way. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]This Group was
[normal] set up by, involves, and reports to 
[normal]the CEOs of the three 
[normal]main operators of helicopter services in the North Sea
[normal]. 
[normal]T
[normal]he JOR 
[normal]is 
[normal]to become the principal vehicle for safety improvement cooperation. Its mission is “to review current processes, procedures and equipment in order to identify best practice in the offshore helicopter industry with a view to further enhancing safety”. 
